    "definition": "Alts are alternative jokes, lines of dialogue, or short passages pitched in the [[Writers' room]] as replacements or supplements to existing material in a script.\n\nWhen a line isn't landing — or when the room wants to give the director and editor options — writers pitch alts on the spot. The process is fast and competitive: multiple alts may be thrown out in quick succession, with the showrunner or senior writer selecting the strongest. Alts are usually comedic in nature, though the practice applies equally to dramatic dialogue. The term is virtually synonymous with *alternates* and is standard usage across both half-hour and hour-long production.",
