    "aliases": [
      "burning through story"
    ],
    "definition": "Burning through story is the condition in which a series moves too quickly through its narrative potential — consuming plot and revelation faster than the story world can sustain, at the expense of character depth and credibility. The term is a critique: shows that burn through story risk losing audience trust when the pace of revelation outstrips believable character reaction.",
