    "ru": "Candy bag",
    "ready": true,
    "en": "Candy bag",
    "clusters": [],
    "aliases": [
      "candy bag"
    ],
    "definition": "The candy bag is an informal archive of discarded jokes, bits, and story ideas set aside during the writing process for potential use in future episodes.\n\nThe concept acknowledges that good material cut from one episode — for reasons of pace, tone, or fit — rarely deserves to be thrown away entirely. Instead, it is collected and held for the right moment elsewhere in the series. The practice is particularly useful in comedy, where a joke that doesn't land in one context may be exactly right in another, but the principle applies equally to dramatic beats or [[Subplot]] ideas. Maintaining a candy bag encourages writers to cut freely, knowing that useful material has a second chance rather than disappearing into a deleted draft.",
