    "ru": "Catharsis",
    "ready": true,
    "en": "Catharsis",
    "clusters": [],
    "aliases": [
      "catharsis"
    ],
    "definition": "Catharsis (Aristotle's term) is the emotional release or purging that effective storytelling generates in an audience. All effective storytelling creates an active conversation between the characters' actions and the audience's emotional response — laughter, tears, outrage, fear. The audience's responses to what characters do, say, and experience constitute the cathartic effect that is the ultimate goal of narrative.",
