    "ru": "Hero's journey",
    "ready": true,
    "en": "Hero's journey",
    "clusters": [],
    "aliases": [
      "hero's journey",
      "monomyth"
    ],
    "definition": "The hero's journey is a circular narrative structure in which a hero starts at home, receives a summons to adventure in a special world, resists the call, is forced to go, faces escalating trials and enemies, passes through an inner sanctum where they confront death, claims a treasure, and returns to the normal world transformed. On the way the hero encounters [[Archetype]]s — mentor, threshold guardian, herald, shape-shifter, shadow, and trickster. The journey ends with the hero returning home with the treasure, having been changed by the experience.",
    "notes": "",
    "comments": []
