    "ru": "Previously on",
    "ready": true,
    "en": "Previously on",
    "clusters": [],
    "aliases": [
      "previously on"
    ],
    "definition": "\"Previously on…\" is the brief recap sequence that opens a serialised episode, recapping earlier story events before the new episode begins.\n\nIts dual purpose is to orient first-time or lapsed viewers while reminding loyal ones of the threads that matter for what follows. The sequence is most common in dramas with a strong [[Subplot]] and serialised [[Story structure]], where continuity across episodes is essential to [[Suspense]] and payoff. In procedurals or anthology formats with little serialisation, it is rarely needed. As streaming platforms made full-season binge-watching the norm, the \"previously on\" became both more selective — cueing only the beats relevant to the coming episode — and, in some cases, optional, since platforms expect viewers to watch episodes back-to-back. In short-form or [[Web series]] formats it is often omitted entirely for pacing reasons.\n\nThe sequence is assembled in post-production but its content is shaped by the [[Writers' room]]: which details a new viewer must understand, which unresolved [[Stakes]] need refreshing, and which emotional context is required for the [[Teaser]] that follows.",
    "notes": "",
    "comments": []
