    "ru": "Web series",
    "ready": true,
    "en": "Web series",
    "clusters": [],
    "aliases": [
      "web series",
      "webisode",
      "short-form series",
      "webisodes"
    ],
    "definition": "A web series is a short-form narrative video series, typically low or no budget. Episodes (sometimes called webisodes) generally run between three and ten minutes — averaging five to six minutes for comedy, seven to nine for drama. Web series are often used as calling cards to demonstrate a creator's voice, or as pitch reels to sell a longer-form series to a streaming platform or network. Distribution is primarily via online platforms (YouTube, Hulu, Crackle, etc.).",
